CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. 2, reads: "Next Goode Pharmacy - The three-story building shown above, located at Frankstown and Brushton Aves., has been purchased by William W. Goode and will be the home of Goode's Corner Pharmacy, when he vacates the property at Fullerton St. and Wylie Ave. Speculation was silenced when Mr. Goode told The Courier that he had bought the Homewood building from Mrs. Sarah Shear for $31,000. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Al and Nat's Market, future home of Goode Pharmacy, on corner of Frankstown and Brushton Avenues, Homewood
